---
<section id="meridian" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-24">
  <div class="section-label mb-4">§3 — The first implementation</div>
  <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight max-w-3xl">
    Meridian-Canon.
  </h2>
  <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
    A Canon-conformant architecture for a personal digital archive — every text message, email, document, voicemail, and file a person possesses — ingested, normalized, enriched, indexed, and attested. Every retrieval is a self-verifying JSON artifact.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
    <div>
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-4">What it does</h3>
      <ol class="space-y-3 text-ink-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">1.</span>
          <span>Ingests every source — phone backup, Gmail, iCloud, Dropbox, local archive — into one SQLite database with cryptographic hashes.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">2.</span>
          <span>Reads every document with a local language model, extracting structured claims with explicit inference types and acknowledged gaps.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">3.</span>
          <span>Challenges its own conclusions via five adversarial tests before sealing anything.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-cardinal-600 shrink-0">4.</span>
          <span>Answers natural-language questions with sealed <code>SearchAttestation</code>s. Produces <code>BriefAttestation</code>s for evidentiary synthesis.</span>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-4">Scale</h3>
      <dl class="space-y-3 text-ink-600">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4">
          <dt class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-500">corpus</dt>
          <dd>~3×10<sup>5</sup> primary documents</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4">
          <dt class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-500">vectors</dt>
          <dd>~5×10<sup>5</sup>–10<sup>6</sup> after chunking</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4">
          <dt class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-500">compute</dt>
          <dd>~8 dev-days + ~$10 GPU time</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4">
          <dt class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-500">output</dt>
          <dd>one SQLite file · portable · court-admissible</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/meridian-canon-executive-summary.pdf">Read the exec summary (PDF)</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
